\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f0\fs22\lang9 What is Table?\par
The HTML tables are used to present data in grid manner like row and columns. Using Bootstrap you can greatly improve the appearance of table in a quick and easy way.\par
\par
See the tutorial on HTML tables to learn more about tables.\par
\par
Creating a Simple Table with Bootstrap\par
You can create tables with basic styling that has horizontal dividers and small cell padding (8px by default), by just adding the Bootstrap's class .table to the <table> element.\par
\par
ExampleTry this code \'bb\par
<!DOCTYPE html>\par
<html lang="en">\par
<head>\par
<meta charset="utf-8">\par
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">\par
<title>Bootstrap Simple Table</title>\par
<link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">\par
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>\par
</head>\par
<body>\par
<div class="m-4">\par
    <table class="table">\par
        <thead>\par
            <tr>\par
                <th>#</th>\par
                <th>First Name</th>\par
                <th>Last Name</th>\par
                <th>Email</th>\par
            </tr>\par
        </thead>\par
        <tbody>\par
            <tr>\par
                <td>1</td>\par
                <td>Clark</td>\par
                <td>Kent</td>\par
                <td>clarkkent@mail.com</td>\par
            </tr>\par
            <tr>\par
                <td>2</td>\par
                <td>Peter</td>\par
                <td>Parker</td>\par
                <td>peterparker@mail.com</td>\par
            </tr>\par
            <tr>\par
                <td>3</td>\par
                <td>John</td>\par
                <td>Carter</td>\par
                <td>johncarter@mail.com</td>\par
            </tr>\par
        </tbody>\par
    </table>\par
</div>\par
</body>\par
</html>\par
